library(ggplot2)
data= read.csv("total-scores2.csv")
d=data$TOXICITY

###### number5########
a=d[2348:2398]
b=d[2400:2450]



p1=boxplot(a, b, ylab="Toxicity Score",
names=c("Before","After"),
main="Instance 5")

t.test(a, b)
## 
##  Welch Two Sample t-test
## 
## data:  a and b
## t = -2.5191, df = 97.538, p-value = 0.01339
## alternative hypothesis: true difference in means is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  -0.13841770 -0.01642878
## sample estimates:
## mean of x mean of y 
## 0.1611204 0.2385436
shapiro.test(a)
## 
##  Shapiro-Wilk normality test
## 
## data:  a
## W = 0.72844, p-value = 2.226e-08
shapiro.test(b)
## 
##  Shapiro-Wilk normality test
## 
## data:  b
## W = 0.88465, p-value = 0.0001343
library("ggpubr")
## Warning: package 'ggpubr' was built under R version 4.0.4
ggqqplot(a, ylab = "Toxicity Score-Before",title="Instance 5",
         ggtheme = theme_minimal())

ggqqplot(b, ylab = "Toxicity Score-After",title="Instance 5",
         ggtheme = theme_minimal())
